## 1. The model: 1 manager + departments (separate sessions)
You are the **bus**: sessions don't talk to each other — you carry the messages.

| Session | What it does | How you launch it | Entry file |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Manager** | decides, plans, triages, writes sprints, commits/pushes | `/lancia-org` ({{MANAGER_MODEL}}) | — (you talk to it) |
| **Execution** | writes code, runs the micros | `/lancia-operativa <work-order>` | `ActualStatus.md` + `Sprint.md` (re-read from disk) |
| **<Dept>** | <its mandate> | `/lancia-<dept>` | `<dept>/CHARTER.md` + `<dept>/INTERFACE.md` |

**Golden rule:** anything **decision / strategy / price** comes back to the **manager**. Departments outside their lane **don't decide** — they escalate (through you).

### ⚡ Slash commands (no more pasting prompts)
Open a new session and type the command as the **first message**; it expands into the right prompt (which reads its charter + interface + current task from disk). Tasks live in files, so the commands **don't expire**.

| Command | Session | Open in | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| `/lancia-org` | Manager | {{MANAGER_MODEL}} | self-orients (reads state + interfaces) |
| `/lancia-operativa <work-order>` | Execution | model per work-order | e.g. `/lancia-operativa Refactor X` |
| `/lancia-<dept>` | Department | per recipe | runs its open `From Manager` items |
| `/lancia-ricerca <brief>` | Research | strong model | one-off deep research |
| `/bootstrap` | Manager | {{MANAGER_MODEL}} | (re)generate instance files by interview |

> ⚠️ **Rooting rule:** open **every** session from `{{PROJECT_ROOT}}` — never another repo/worktree. Otherwise git points at the wrong repo, slash commands are "Unknown command", and "read from disk" fails.

## 2. How we work together (the cycle)
1. **Come to the manager** when you need a decision, have a department output to triage, want to plan a step, or finished a block.
2. **It prepares** the work (work-order/runbook/prompt) and updates the sprints.
3. **You launch** the right session with the pointer it gives you.
4. That session works and **hands you an output** → you relay it → it triages, updates files, decides next.
5. **Commits/pushes are the manager's**, with your OK to push.

## 3. Where to find things (file map)
**State & planning (open often):**
- `ActualStatus.md` — where we are, one page (auto-loaded).
- `Sprint.md` — all sprints, micros, work-orders.
- `Sprint_Done.md` — closed history.

**Knowledge folders:**
- `research/` — research briefs + outputs (index: `research/README.md`).
- `reference/` — durable reference docs (architecture, business, specs).
- `incidents/` — post-mortems.

**Departments (entry file + ledger + channel):**
- `<dept>/CHARTER.md` (its rules), `<dept>/STATUS.md` (ledger), `<dept>/INTERFACE.md` (channel).

**Reference (consult when needed):**
- `CLAUDE.md` (process rules) · `bottega.config.md` (your config) · `AUTOMATION_PLAYBOOK.md` (what we automate, when, behind which gates) · any project docs.

